-- Encana Sells 50% Cutbank Stake to PetroChina for C$5.4 Billion
-- B y   J e r a n   W i t t e n s t e i n
-- 2011-02-09T22:16:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-09/encana-sells-50-stake-in-cutbank-business-to-petrochina-for-5-44-billion.html
  Encana Corp ., Canada’s largest
natural-gas producer, agreed to sell a 50 percent stake in the
company’s Cutbank Ridge business to a PetroChina Co. unit for
C$5.4 billion ($5.44 billion).  The agreement creates a joint venture with PetroChina
International Investment that includes assets in British
Columbia and Alberta.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jeran Wittenstein at 
 jwittenstei1@bloomberg.net  